Title : Arnhild Skre
Text : '''Arnhild Johanna Skre''' (born 19 May 1952) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] newspaper editor, press historian and biographer.

She was born in [[Bergen]]. She finished her secondary education in 1971 and the [[Nansen Academy]] in 1972. In 1977 she graduated from the [[University of Oslo]] with the [[cand.mag.]] degree in social anthropology, ethnology and history. In 1978 she studied at the [[University of Iceland]].<ref name=pf1997>{{cite book|editor-link=Nils E. Øy|editor=Øy, Nils E.|title=Pressefolk 1997|year=1998 |publisher=Institute for Journalism|location=Fredrikstad|language=Norwegian|page=328|chapter=Skre, Arnhild}}</ref> In 2003 she took the [[cand.philol.]] degree in history.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Arnhild Skre|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=|location=|url=http://www.snl.no/Arnhild_Skre|language=Norwegian|accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref>

She worked in [[NRK|NRK Hordaland]] from 1979 to 1983, and was then a freelancer for NRK, ''[[Dag og Tid]]'' and ''Jeg'' until 1986. She was then hired permanently in the weekly ''Dag og Tid'', and was its editor-in-chief from 1990 to 1994.<ref name=pf1997/> From 1995 to 1999 she led the cultural feature desk of ''[[Aftenposten]]''.<ref name=snl/>

She chaired ''Norsk Pressehistorisk Forening'' from 2003 to 2010 and edited the journal ''Pressehistorisk tidsskrift'' from 2010<ref name=snl/> to 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pressehistorisk.no/index.asp?id=123746 |title=Redaktørskifte i Pressehistorisk Tidsskrift |date=7 January 2014 |publisher=Norsk Pressehistorisk Forening |language=Norwegian |accessdate=26 April 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426202157/http://www.pressehistorisk.no/index.asp?id=123746 |archivedate=26 April 2014 }}</ref> She released a biography on [[Ragnhild Jølsen]] in 2008 and [[Hulda Garborg]] in 2011. The latter won the [[Brage Prize]]. She also contributed to 2010's ''[[Norsk presses historie 1660–2010]]''.<ref name=snl/>

She resides in [[Ytre Enebakk]] and is married to [[Nils Butenschøn]].<ref name=snl/>

